{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Rwanda", "text_new": "{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Rwanda}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Rwanda\n| map1 = \n| legend1 = \n| map2 = \n| legend2 = \n| map3 = \n| legend3 = \n| disease = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location = [[Rwanda]]\n| first_case = [[Kigali]]\n| arrival_date = 14 March 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=03|day1=14|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin = [[Wuhan]], [[China]]\n| recovery_cases = 25\n| deaths = 0\n| confirmed_cases = 125<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://twitter.com/RwandaHealth/status/1249398203545419776?s=19 |title=12.04.2020Amakuru Mashya kuri Koronavirusi COVID-19 / Update on COVID-19 Coronavirus / Mise \u00e0 Jour sur le Coronavirus COVID-19pic.twitter.com/In0PukkSvZ |last=Rwanda |first=Ministry of Health |date=2020-04-12 |website=@RwandaHealth |language=ro |access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n| total_ili = \n| website = \n}}\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have reached [[Rwanda]] in March 2020.\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n==Timeline==\n===March 2020===\nThe first case of [[COVID-19]] in Rwanda was confirmed on 14 March 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Rwanda confirms first case of coronavirus - health ministry|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-rwanda/rwanda-confirms-first-case-of-coronavirus-health-ministry-idUSKBN2110G0|website=Reuters|date=14 March 2020|accessdate=14 March 2020|language=en|last=|publisher=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314143042/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-rwanda/rwanda-confirms-first-case-of-coronavirus-health-ministry-idUSKBN2110G0|archive-date=14 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Four other people were tested after the first case tested positive, bringing the number of cases to five.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/gahuza/amakuru-51904449|title=Abanduye coronavirus mu Rwanda babaye batanu|date=16 March 2020|work=BBC News Gahuza|access-date=18 March 2020|language=rw}}</ref>\n\nBy 16 March 2020, Rwanda confirmed two more cases in [[Kigali]], bringing the total number of cases in the country to seven.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theeastafrican.co.ke/scienceandhealth/Rwanda-coronavirus-cases/3073694-5493772-156tke0/index.html|title=Rwanda confirms seventh coronavirus case|website=The East African|language=en|access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref> In an attempt to stop the coronavirus, Rwandan officials announced a two-week lockdown. Both public and private employees are to work from home, under strict measures. All borders are also to be closed, cargo and Rwandan nationals being exempt, with a mandatory 14-day quarantine.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/africa/rwanda-in-lockdown-to-contain-coronavirus/1774850|title=Rwanda in lockdown to contain coronavirus|website=www.aa.com.tr|access-date=23 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/africa/rwanda-steps-up-efforts-to-beat-coronavirus/1774728|title=Rwanda steps up efforts to beat coronavirus|website=www.aa.com.tr|access-date=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Ministry of Health]] on 28 March recorded six new COVID-19 cases, taking the total of those diagnosed with the virus to 60.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newtimes.co.rw/news/rwanda-covid-19-cases-increase-60-all-patients-recovering-well|title=Rwanda COVID-19 cases increase to 60; all patients recovering well|last=Kuteesa |first=Hudson |date=28 March 2020 |work=The New Times |url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=29 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== April 2020 ===\nOn 9 April, three new cases of coronavirus were identified, out of 720 samples examined in the past 24 hours. This brings the total balance of confirmed cases to 113 people (of which 7 have recovered).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.alwihdainfo.com/Coronavirus-Rwanda-Mise-a-jour-sur-le-coronavirus-COVID-19-9-avril-2020_a85594.html|title=Coronavirus - Rwanda : Mise \u00e0 jour sur le coronavirus COVID-19 - 9 avril 2020|website=Alwihda Info - Actualit\u00e9s TCHAD, Afrique, International|language=fr|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Africa]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Rwanda]]\n[[Category:2020 in Rwanda|Coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Africa|Rwanda]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Rwanda]]\n\n\n{{rwanda-stub}}\n{{COVID-19-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Rwanda}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Rwanda\n| map1 = \n| legend1 = \n| map2 = \n| legend2 = \n| map3 = \n| legend3 = \n| disease = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location = [[Rwanda]]\n| first_case = [[Kigali]]\n| arrival_date = 14 March 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=03|day1=14|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin = [[Wuhan]], [[China]]\n| recovery_cases = 25\n| deaths = 0\n| confirmed_cases = 125<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://twitter.com/RwandaHealth/status/1249398203545419776?s=19 |title=12.04.2020Amakuru Mashya kuri Koronavirusi COVID-19 / Update on COVID-19 Coronavirus / Mise \u00e0 Jour sur le Coronavirus COVID-19pic.twitter.com/In0PukkSvZ |last=Rwanda |first=Ministry of Health |date=2020-04-12 |website=@RwandaHealth |language=ro |access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n| total_ili = \n| website = \n}}\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have reached [[Rwanda]] in March 2020.\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n==Timeline==\n===March 2020===\nThe first case of [[COVID-19]] in Rwanda was confirmed on 14 March 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Rwanda confirms first case of coronavirus - health ministry|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-rwanda/rwanda-confirms-first-case-of-coronavirus-health-ministry-idUSKBN2110G0|website=Reuters|date=14 March 2020|accessdate=14 March 2020|language=en|last=|publisher=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314143042/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-rwanda/rwanda-confirms-first-case-of-coronavirus-health-ministry-idUSKBN2110G0|archive-date=14 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Four other people were tested after the first case tested positive, bringing the number of cases to five.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/gahuza/amakuru-51904449|title=Abanduye coronavirus mu Rwanda babaye batanu|date=16 March 2020|work=BBC News Gahuza|access-date=18 March 2020|language=rw}}</ref>\n\nBy 16 March 2020, Rwanda confirmed two more cases in [[Kigali]], bringing the total number of cases in the country to seven.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theeastafrican.co.ke/scienceandhealth/Rwanda-coronavirus-cases/3073694-5493772-156tke0/index.html|title=Rwanda confirms seventh coronavirus case|website=The East African|language=en|access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref> In an attempt to stop the coronavirus, Rwandan officials announced a two-week lockdown. Both public and private employees are to work from home, under strict measures. All borders are also to be closed, cargo and Rwandan nationals being exempt, with a mandatory 14-day quarantine.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/africa/rwanda-in-lockdown-to-contain-coronavirus/1774850|title=Rwanda in lockdown to contain coronavirus|website=www.aa.com.tr|access-date=23 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/africa/rwanda-steps-up-efforts-to-beat-coronavirus/1774728|title=Rwanda steps up efforts to beat coronavirus|website=www.aa.com.tr|access-date=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Ministry of Health]] on 28 March recorded six new COVID-19 cases, taking the total of those diagnosed with the virus to 60.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newtimes.co.rw/news/rwanda-covid-19-cases-increase-60-all-patients-recovering-well|title=Rwanda COVID-19 cases increase to 60; all patients recovering well|last=Kuteesa |first=Hudson |date=28 March 2020 |work=The New Times |url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=29 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== April 2020 ===\nOn 9 April, 3 new cases of coronavirus were identified today, out of 720 samples examined in the past 24 hours. This brings the total balance of confirmed cases to 113 people (of which 7 have recovered).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.alwihdainfo.com/Coronavirus-Rwanda-Mise-a-jour-sur-le-coronavirus-COVID-19-9-avril-2020_a85594.html|title=Coronavirus - Rwanda : Mise \u00e0 jour sur le coronavirus COVID-19 - 9 avril 2020|website=Alwihda Info - Actualit\u00e9s TCHAD, Afrique, International|language=fr|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Africa]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Rwanda]]\n[[Category:2020 in Rwanda|Coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Africa|Rwanda]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Rwanda]]\n\n\n{{rwanda-stub}}\n{{COVID-19-stub}}\n", "name_user": "CRau080", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eApril 2020", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Rwanda"}
